KOKO: In view of a recent protest, followed by  publications in some national newspapers and social media platforms by the Oghara Traditional Council, alleging an illegal and unlawful handing over of vast expanse of land belonging to  Oghara, located at Otegbo ( which the Itsekiri call Obitugbo) village to the Nigeria Army by His Royal Majesty , Ogiame Atuwatse III, The Olu of Warri Kingdom, the people of Obitugbo Community, through the Obitugbo Community Management Committee in Warri North local government area of Delta State, have reacted by imploring the Oghara people to pursue their case with legal option rather than resort to  intimidation and threat of war, remarking that, should there be any unprovoked attack from the Oghara people, they Obitugbo Community, though peace loving would have no other option but to defend themselves.The Obitugbo people also urged the Delta State Governor, His Excellency, Dr. Senator Ifeanyi Okowa, to discountenance the said  publication, describing it as alleged ” vituperation” and  a ” storm in a tea cup”.  In a six page rejoinder entitled: “Re: Illegal And  Unlawful Handing  Over  Of Vast Expanse  Of Land  Belonging To Oghara , Located  At Otegbo  ( Which The  Itsekiri Call Obitugbo) Village To The Nigeria  Army  By His Royal Majesty,  Ogiame Atuwatse III, The Olu  Of Warri Kingdom”, and signed by: Justice Akuyoma, Chairman; Esanye Luke Ariyoh, Secretary and Pa Isaac Jemide, Olare – Aja, on behalf of Obitugbo Community Management Committee, the people remarked that the disputed land belong to Obitugbo Community and His Royal Majesty, Ogiame Atuwatse III, is the overlord of all  Itsekiri land, and therefore,  does nothing wrong in consenting to the wish of his subjects on land under his overlordship rights.In the rejoinder they Obitugbo people claimed that the site for the proposed University of Warri, as well as other institutions are on land owned by the Obitugbo Community.They also cited that Obitugbo is an Itsekiri Community founded by Iyatsere Egharegbemi, who lived there with his wives , children and domestics, that his descendants exercised many acts of possession and ownership over Obite-Ugbo  and it’s still inhabited to this day by his descendants.They cautioned that the issue of dispute arising from  ownership of land can only be  determined by the courts, a path which they Obitugbo people have chosen, instead of resulting to threat of war.They  also  remarked that  on the issue of administrative boundary between Ethiope West and Warri North of wish the Oghara people had been to court, they have also allegedly been roundly defeated as their case was allegedly struck out due to lack of merit.It should be recalled that the Oghara Traditional Council led by HRM King Noble Eshemitan, Uku Oghara name, the Ovie of Oghara Kingdom, on the 5th of April, 2022, had called on the Delta state Governor, Senator Ifeanyi Okowa, to intervene in the ownership of the disputed land located at Ajagbodudu and Otegbo (which the Itsekiri call Obitugbo) villages between the Urhobos of Oghara Kingdom in Ethiope West Local government area  and the Itsekiris in Warri North local government area, both in Delta State.They also accused the Itsekiris of planning to establish a private university in the Oghara land territory of